Regular expressions are designed to code or replace strings or extract strings
from a string by placing a template that meets certain criteria and estimating
that we do not know the value but only the template that the string is supposed to be.
Most modern programming languages, such as javascript, php, nodejs, mysql and more,
have adopted the Perl Compatible Regular Expressions (PCRE) standard. means,
the syntax of the perl language: the markers and templates of the regular expressions.
